Syrian White Helmet rescuer who saved 'miracle baby' is killed in Aleppo airstrike 
A Syrian rescue worker who became famous around the world after saving a baby buried for 16 hours under rubble has been killed in an airstrike. 
Khaled Omar, 31, was a member ofthe White Helmets, a Syrian civil defence group that has rescued countless civilians during the country's five-year civil war.
In 2014, he was at the centre of a "miracle baby drama" when he was filmed saving a baby boy from the bombed-out remains of a home in Aleppo. 